WEBVTT

00:49.720 --> 00:51.850
Mr. Fatty, she has princess syndrome.

00:52.120 --> 00:54.200
She's always trying to get my attention.

00:54.200 --> 00:56.440
Every now and then, she snatches

00:56.880 --> 00:58.610
some shiny things from my desk.

00:59.040 --> 01:00.770
I'll give you plenty to pick up.

01:02.400 --> 01:03.680
What about the other pieces?

01:03.680 --> 01:05.519
It's good enough that I got this porcelain piece back.

01:05.519 --> 01:07.320
The rest can't be found anymore.

01:42.240 --> 01:42.840
Mr. Zhang,

01:43.720 --> 01:44.850
can I say a few words?

01:45.000 --> 01:45.800
Wait a moment.

01:48.039 --> 01:48.570
Go ahead.

01:49.080 --> 01:49.880
Dear viewers.

01:50.640 --> 01:52.640
I am from Jingdezhen Ceramic University,

01:52.640 --> 01:54.360
a teacher of the restoration major.

01:54.360 --> 01:55.490
My name is Yue Qixin.

01:55.840 --> 01:58.600
I take full responsibility for what I am about to say.

01:58.600 --> 01:59.660
Please take a look.

02:00.360 --> 02:02.720
This is a broken piece we found in the shop,

02:03.040 --> 02:04.880
from the porcelain bowl

02:05.280 --> 02:07.320
that was personally smashed

02:07.320 --> 02:08.360
by Mr. Zhang.

02:08.759 --> 02:11.290
There are obvious traces of splicing on this.

02:11.800 --> 02:13.060
Instrument tests show

02:13.480 --> 02:14.480
that the old part,

02:14.480 --> 02:16.000
just as Mr. Zhang said,

02:17.040 --> 02:20.640
is an old bowl bottom from the Chenghua reign of the Ming Dynasty.

02:20.840 --> 02:23.320
But the new part is clearly a replica.

02:24.040 --> 02:24.900
This indicates

02:25.079 --> 02:28.210
that the porcelain bowl Mr. Zhang smashed was rejoined.

02:29.120 --> 02:31.320
This also proves that what Xu Xiao

02:32.240 --> 02:33.680
said to you two at the time

02:34.280 --> 02:35.240
was correct.

02:36.400 --> 02:37.730
Everyone, please look.

02:38.360 --> 02:38.720
This

02:40.000 --> 02:43.530
is the certificate issued by the Ceramics Research Institute.

02:51.000 --> 02:51.600
Mr. Zhang.

02:52.560 --> 02:55.800
This farce should come to an end now.

02:56.600 --> 02:58.640
And please, from now on,

02:59.079 --> 03:00.320
stop slandering Xu Xiao

03:00.320 --> 03:02.380
and Jingdezhen Ceramic University.

03:02.880 --> 03:03.600
Otherwise,

03:04.160 --> 03:07.360
you will face legal sanctions and punishment.

03:08.440 --> 03:09.520
Do you understand?

03:13.640 --> 03:14.640
In most cases,

03:15.520 --> 03:18.050
people can only see the world they want to see.

03:19.040 --> 03:21.900
They only believe what they are willing to believe.

03:22.160 --> 03:23.220
If this continues,

03:23.400 --> 03:25.280
they will fall into a vicious circle,

03:25.280 --> 03:27.360
trapping themselves inside and unable to get out.

03:27.360 --> 03:29.420
I don't want to see this happen again.

03:58.840 --> 04:00.040
So the issue with Xu Xiao

04:00.040 --> 04:01.360
is completely resolved now, right?

04:01.360 --> 04:04.220
I saw Zhang Jiatian apologizing on the live stream.

04:04.480 --> 04:05.840
Many buyers are demanding a refund.

04:05.840 --> 04:06.700
He apologized.

04:06.760 --> 04:08.960
Evil people will get their retribution.

04:08.960 --> 04:09.490
Exactly.

04:10.040 --> 04:11.360
He's here.

04:17.040 --> 04:17.680
Clap.

04:20.040 --> 04:20.399
Mr. Yue.

04:20.399 --> 04:21.440
You live up to your name, Mr. Yue.

04:21.440 --> 04:22.120
Hello, Mr. Yue.

04:22.120 --> 04:23.040
You look so handsome, Mr. Yue.

04:23.040 --> 04:23.360
Good.

04:23.360 --> 04:23.720
So handsome.

04:23.720 --> 04:24.960
Mr. Yue. Mr. Yue.

04:26.760 --> 04:28.290
As expected of you, Mr. Yue.

04:30.000 --> 04:30.640
So cool.

04:30.640 --> 04:31.640
It has to be Mr. Yue.

04:31.640 --> 04:32.120
Mr. Yue,

04:35.680 --> 04:36.280
thank you.

04:38.400 --> 04:39.440
All right, get up.

04:40.760 --> 04:43.159
You should thank your classmates the most.

04:43.280 --> 04:44.080
Yes.

04:44.600 --> 04:46.400
Give another round of applause.

04:49.159 --> 04:49.720
Go back.

04:50.400 --> 04:51.560
Alright, class.

04:51.840 --> 04:52.320
Okay.

04:52.640 --> 04:53.040
Let's begin class.

04:53.040 --> 04:53.570
Alright.

05:03.680 --> 05:05.720
The victim was found at the beverage station on the third floor of the annex.

05:05.720 --> 05:07.840
The door to the beverage station opens inward,

05:07.840 --> 05:09.170
and could not be opened.

05:09.320 --> 05:11.120
The windows were also locked from the inside.

05:11.120 --> 05:13.180
So this was a completely locked room.

05:13.440 --> 05:14.480
The solution to this case,

05:14.480 --> 05:16.080
which is also the only solution,

05:16.080 --> 05:18.200
is that the killer took advantage of everyone's fixed mindset.

05:18.200 --> 05:21.000
To create the illusion that he had just arrived at the crime scene.

05:21.000 --> 05:21.560
In fact,

05:22.080 --> 05:24.360
he had been hiding in the wine cabinet and never left.

05:24.360 --> 05:25.240
And among us,

05:25.640 --> 05:29.100
the only person who had the chance to hide in the wine cabinet is

05:29.200 --> 05:29.860
Lin Yuexin.

05:34.560 --> 05:36.480
I think we can just vote for the killer.

05:36.480 --> 05:39.409
There's no need to proceed with the following steps.

05:41.560 --> 05:43.890
I think we shouldn't invite him next time.

05:48.480 --> 05:50.010
My back hurts from sitting.

05:50.480 --> 05:51.640
Nothing I can do.

05:52.400 --> 05:54.800
I got caught my first time being the killer.

05:54.880 --> 05:55.520
Yan Xue,

05:56.159 --> 05:57.159
wait a moment.

05:57.880 --> 05:58.680
What's wrong?

06:03.960 --> 06:05.440
I want to give this to you.

06:09.600 --> 06:11.720
Xu Xiao and I fixed this together.

06:12.720 --> 06:13.580
My assignment.

06:14.440 --> 06:15.480
About what happened before, I...

06:15.480 --> 06:16.120
I'm sorry.

06:20.160 --> 06:20.800
First,

06:21.120 --> 06:23.520
I want to thank you for fixing my porcelain.

06:23.520 --> 06:25.450
Second, I want to apologize to you.

06:26.400 --> 06:27.000
But I hope

06:27.000 --> 06:28.860
you can understand why I did that.

06:28.880 --> 06:30.080
I thought you liked Xu Xiao

06:30.080 --> 06:31.160
but were deliberately hiding it.

06:31.160 --> 06:32.200
That day, you said you wouldn't team up with him,

06:32.200 --> 06:33.600
but the next day, you did.

06:33.600 --> 06:35.040
We all thought you were being two-faced,

06:35.040 --> 06:36.159
so we were really angry.

06:36.159 --> 06:36.920
But over time,

06:36.920 --> 06:38.760
I realized you genuinely didn't know.

06:38.760 --> 06:40.280
So I want to apologize to you.

06:40.280 --> 06:40.800
I mean,

06:41.880 --> 06:43.159
can you just face

06:43.159 --> 06:44.290
your true feelings?

06:45.200 --> 06:45.560
I...

06:45.560 --> 06:46.090
Besides,

06:46.440 --> 06:48.000
I think Xu Xiao likes you.

06:48.600 --> 06:49.480
No, he's just...

06:49.480 --> 06:50.940
If Xu Xiao didn't like you,

06:51.159 --> 06:51.600
think about it,

06:51.600 --> 06:53.600
why would he team up with you? Right?

06:53.600 --> 06:54.159
So,

06:55.000 --> 06:56.720
can you accept my apology?

06:59.280 --> 06:59.840
Yes.

07:00.560 --> 07:02.240
Then let's hug.

07:03.400 --> 07:03.920
Okay.

07:09.760 --> 07:10.290
Let's go.

07:10.520 --> 07:10.920
Okay.

07:12.400 --> 07:12.930
Let's go.

07:32.760 --> 07:34.560
It's time to take your medicine.

08:00.280 --> 08:01.210
Here, take this.

08:02.080 --> 08:05.040
Why is there always candy when I take medicine?

08:06.600 --> 08:07.730
I like sweet things.

08:07.800 --> 08:09.600
I usually keep some in my pocket.

08:58.280 --> 09:00.320
Crackle glaze refers to

09:00.320 --> 09:03.000
a natural cracking phenomenon on porcelain glaze.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.660
This was originally a flaw in firing porcelain.

09:06.200 --> 09:08.400
But after people mastered the pattern,

09:08.440 --> 09:10.040
they created crackle glaze.

09:11.240 --> 09:12.400
The cracked surface

09:12.520 --> 09:14.960
presents a unique beauty instead.

09:16.200 --> 09:17.260
On the road of life,

09:17.480 --> 09:19.400
there will be many forks.

09:20.320 --> 09:22.720
But it is exactly these countless branches

09:22.840 --> 09:24.280
that make us complete.

10:30.320 --> 10:31.320
His excellence,

10:31.640 --> 10:33.570
and an inexplicable persistence,

10:35.040 --> 10:36.640
are very attractive, right?

10:38.120 --> 10:39.360
Can you face

10:39.360 --> 10:40.560
your true feelings?

10:46.240 --> 10:47.600
Let's give it a name.

10:48.400 --> 10:50.000
Is Xiaoqing okay?

11:25.640 --> 11:27.640
Hello, everyone. My name is Xu Xiao.

11:27.960 --> 11:29.090
Nice to meet you all.

11:29.200 --> 11:29.800
Thank you.

11:37.240 --> 11:38.320
Can I team up

11:38.800 --> 11:39.560
with you?

11:45.760 --> 11:46.200
Here.

12:04.760 --> 12:08.800
So this is what it feels like to fall for someone.

12:35.640 --> 12:36.080
Mom.

12:38.600 --> 12:39.260
Have a seat.

12:47.440 --> 12:48.570
Have some tea first.

12:50.840 --> 12:52.760
You asked me out behind Uncle Song's back.

12:52.760 --> 12:54.020
Instead of going home,

12:54.040 --> 12:55.440
we're drinking tea here.

13:02.760 --> 13:03.760
Did you watch

13:04.480 --> 13:05.960
Zhang Jiatian's live stream?

13:05.960 --> 13:06.690
Actually...

13:06.760 --> 13:08.220
I know what you want to say.

13:09.480 --> 13:10.610
Out of the question.

13:16.560 --> 13:19.420
Actually, I've always been able to understand you.

13:23.920 --> 13:25.450
You don't want me to suffer,

13:26.640 --> 13:27.970
or to be in this industry

13:29.040 --> 13:30.600
and be looked down upon

13:31.080 --> 13:32.410
because of what Dad did.

13:32.600 --> 13:35.560
You certainly don't want me to follow in his footsteps.

13:35.560 --> 13:36.200
But Mom,

13:37.920 --> 13:38.850
I want to tell you

13:42.440 --> 13:44.840
that I could never become someone like him.

13:46.040 --> 13:48.100
I would never do anything to hurt you.

13:49.840 --> 13:52.840
I will absolutely not become obsessed with antiques,

13:54.320 --> 13:55.160
because I know

13:58.000 --> 13:59.520
that would only end up hurting

13:59.520 --> 14:00.920
the people closest to me.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.000
I always remember

14:03.280 --> 14:06.080
when we were in debt when I was a kid.

14:08.280 --> 14:10.680
You struggled alone to support the family,

14:11.720 --> 14:13.120
losing so much hair

14:13.920 --> 14:15.680
and staying awake all night.

14:17.840 --> 14:19.840
But you always smiled at me in the end

14:22.040 --> 14:23.970
and said everything would be fine.

14:26.560 --> 14:28.020
So I've always told myself

14:29.560 --> 14:32.490
that I will absolutely never become a man like my dad,

14:35.520 --> 14:37.650
and I will never let you get hurt again.

14:41.840 --> 14:42.900
Since I was little,

14:43.880 --> 14:45.540
you were the one who raised me.

14:46.120 --> 14:47.200
Even though it was because of Dad

14:47.200 --> 14:49.130
that I fell in love with this major,

14:49.800 --> 14:52.800
you were the one who taught me how to be a decent person.

14:53.040 --> 14:53.440
Mom.

14:54.560 --> 14:55.600
I will study hard

14:56.800 --> 14:58.600
and take everything seriously.

14:59.600 --> 15:00.640
Even when facing controversy,

15:00.640 --> 15:02.370
I must live up to my conscience.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.460
That's what you taught me.

15:06.880 --> 15:09.120
This is not only my respect for the major,

15:09.120 --> 15:10.650
but also my respect for you.

15:12.560 --> 15:13.000
So,

15:14.120 --> 15:14.560
Mom,

15:15.560 --> 15:16.820
I hope you can trust me.

15:19.320 --> 15:20.250
I am not like him.

15:23.000 --> 15:24.730
I will never make you sad again.

15:42.880 --> 15:44.320
The color seems too dark,

15:44.400 --> 15:45.060
doesn't it?

15:45.120 --> 15:45.920
A bit too dark.

15:46.520 --> 15:47.000
No good.

15:47.760 --> 15:49.020
Here, look at this one.

15:52.640 --> 15:53.700
This one is not bad.

15:53.800 --> 15:54.600
The color is nice.

15:54.600 --> 15:56.320
It's too deliberate, Sis.

15:56.920 --> 15:58.120
It's not deliberate.

15:58.520 --> 15:59.640
It's showing respect.

15:59.640 --> 16:01.120
Besides, it's basic courtesy.

16:01.120 --> 16:01.650
You know?

16:02.480 --> 16:03.240
I'm meeting someone for the first time.

16:03.240 --> 16:04.760
I don't want to dress like this.

16:04.760 --> 16:06.480
Plus, I have my own clothes.

16:08.640 --> 16:09.900
What's wrong with you?

16:09.960 --> 16:10.760
You've been like this since we were kids.

16:10.760 --> 16:12.560
You always go against whatever I say.

16:12.560 --> 16:13.000
Let me tell you.

16:13.000 --> 16:14.120
You are not a kid anymore.

16:14.120 --> 16:14.680
Behave.

16:16.160 --> 16:17.120
Mom, Auntie.

16:17.160 --> 16:18.220
What are you doing?

16:18.800 --> 16:21.530
I'm going out with your mom to meet someone later.

16:22.240 --> 16:23.240
Are you going out?

16:23.480 --> 16:24.480
Are you going out?

16:25.440 --> 16:27.120
I'm going out with my classmates.

16:27.120 --> 16:28.640
Isn't it the weekend today?

16:28.640 --> 16:30.300
Why are you running out again?

16:31.040 --> 16:32.400
It's a good thing that Xiaocen can make friends here,

16:32.400 --> 16:33.640
sister.

16:34.280 --> 16:35.480
I'm leaving now, Mom.

16:36.000 --> 16:36.800
Wait a minute.

16:40.920 --> 16:42.520
Okay, don't forget to drink it.

16:42.520 --> 16:43.200
Got it.

16:43.360 --> 16:43.800
Go ahead.

16:43.800 --> 16:44.440
Bye, Aunt.

16:44.680 --> 16:45.560
Bye.

16:46.920 --> 16:48.160
Be careful on the road.

16:48.160 --> 16:48.880
Got it.

16:50.040 --> 16:52.100
She's so old and still makes me worry.

16:53.920 --> 16:54.880
You too.

16:55.800 --> 16:56.760
Still drinking water?

16:56.760 --> 16:57.620
Hurry up and go.

16:58.160 --> 16:58.560
Stop drinking.

16:58.560 --> 16:58.880
Sister.

16:58.880 --> 17:00.480
Get up quickly. Be a good girl.

17:00.480 --> 17:01.400
I don't want to wear that dress anymore.

17:01.400 --> 17:02.720
Hurry up, stand here.

17:02.960 --> 17:04.960
Come on, listen to me. That's right.

17:10.960 --> 17:12.800
Xiaocen, what are you doing today?

17:12.800 --> 17:14.480
Do you want to come to the Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum to play?

17:14.480 --> 17:15.339
I have arrived.

17:15.599 --> 17:17.119
I'm sorry, Yuexin.

17:17.680 --> 17:19.880
I have to work at the antique shop today.

17:20.000 --> 17:22.280
You have to go to the antique shop on the weekend?

17:22.280 --> 17:24.079
Yeah, Xu Xiao is also in the shop.

17:24.200 --> 17:25.329
I have to go and help.

17:25.839 --> 17:27.560
Oh, I see.

17:27.880 --> 17:28.560
Okay then.

17:28.800 --> 17:30.120
That's it then. Bye.

17:33.000 --> 17:35.080
This is a blue-and-white cloud dragon design vat.

17:35.080 --> 17:37.480
It was made in the Imperial Kiln Factory in the Ming Dynasty.

17:37.480 --> 17:39.000
The work you see now

17:39.000 --> 17:40.680
is a piece restored by later generations.

17:40.680 --> 17:41.480
After the founding of the People's Republic,

17:41.480 --> 17:43.560
We excavated many dragon jar fragments.

17:43.560 --> 17:45.480
Only three have been fully restored.

17:45.480 --> 17:46.840
One is on display here.

17:47.120 --> 17:49.720
Another is at the Jingdezhen Ceramics Museum.

17:54.640 --> 17:55.840
You can guess

17:55.840 --> 17:57.560
what this dragon jar was used for.

17:57.560 --> 17:58.040
For raising fish.

17:58.040 --> 17:59.100
For storing water?

17:59.160 --> 17:59.720
Raising fish.

17:59.720 --> 18:01.320
Right, for storing water.

18:06.480 --> 18:07.040
Xu Xiao.

18:14.400 --> 18:14.930
Morning.

18:15.480 --> 18:16.010
Morning.

18:17.840 --> 18:18.840
Where is the boss?

18:19.080 --> 18:22.140
The boss usually doesn't come to the shop on Saturdays.

18:22.240 --> 18:23.840
It's just the two of us today.

18:25.760 --> 18:26.320
Why?

18:27.920 --> 18:29.320
It's pretty quiet.

18:46.040 --> 18:46.900
Let me help you.

18:48.040 --> 18:49.560
It's fine. Do your own work.

18:49.560 --> 18:50.240
It's okay.

18:50.760 --> 18:52.880
I don't have much to do today anyway.

18:53.920 --> 18:54.560
Okay.

19:00.480 --> 19:01.480
How is my drawing?

19:03.160 --> 19:04.080
Not bad.

19:04.640 --> 19:05.480
Just not bad?

19:06.160 --> 19:07.160
It's pretty good.

19:07.560 --> 19:08.000
Okay.

19:14.880 --> 19:16.080
Um, Xiaocen.

19:17.520 --> 19:19.800
Willing to shed hot blood.

19:21.160 --> 19:21.600
Hello, boss.

19:21.600 --> 19:22.530
You are all here.

19:24.200 --> 19:25.130
Why are you here?

19:25.960 --> 19:27.020
Why can't I be here?

19:28.160 --> 19:30.440
Don't you usually not come to the shop on weekends?

19:30.440 --> 19:32.520
I'm a casual person.

19:35.440 --> 19:36.370
How's business?

19:36.560 --> 19:37.290
No business.

19:38.200 --> 19:39.060
That's normal.

19:45.720 --> 19:46.650
Are you two busy?

19:47.360 --> 19:47.800
Yes.

19:48.280 --> 19:48.880
Very busy.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.040
Boss, is there anything wrong?

19:51.040 --> 19:52.360
Come over and have a cup of tea.

19:52.360 --> 19:54.000
Newly arrived Lu'an Melon Seed tea.

19:54.000 --> 19:54.560
Okay.

19:57.040 --> 19:57.840
What's wrong?

19:59.720 --> 20:00.640
When the boss says to drink tea,

20:00.640 --> 20:01.640
it means he wants to chat.

20:01.640 --> 20:03.160
Isn't chatting good?

20:05.520 --> 20:06.580
You'll know later.

20:07.400 --> 20:07.930
Let's go.

20:09.960 --> 20:11.560
Do you know why I like

20:11.560 --> 20:13.220
hiring you college students?

20:15.400 --> 20:16.160
Because you are

20:16.160 --> 20:17.640
full of youthful vigor.

20:18.000 --> 20:18.520
Being with you,

20:18.520 --> 20:19.760
I feel young myself.

20:20.440 --> 20:22.100
College life is really great.

20:22.160 --> 20:23.120
I still remember

20:23.120 --> 20:24.440
the five guys in my college dorm.

20:24.440 --> 20:26.640
Those five were full of hidden talents.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.260
The guy in the bed diagonally opposite me

20:29.400 --> 20:30.600
had a really big head.

20:30.800 --> 20:31.640
When it rained,

20:31.640 --> 20:33.200
his clothes never got wet.

20:33.560 --> 20:35.160
His head caught all the rain.

20:36.640 --> 20:38.120
The one diagonally opposite me on this side

20:38.120 --> 20:39.000
was extremely handsome.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.280
The most handsome in our class.

20:40.280 --> 20:42.800
He looked exactly like Cai Guoqing when he was young.

20:42.800 --> 20:44.520
We all called him Brother Big Eyes.

20:44.520 --> 20:45.840
The one sleeping head-to-head with me

20:45.840 --> 20:46.560
was smart from a young age

20:46.560 --> 20:47.480
and always tricked me.

20:47.480 --> 20:48.320
At that time, he told me

20:48.320 --> 20:49.040
that in his hometown,

20:49.040 --> 20:49.760
with one whistle,

20:49.760 --> 20:51.490
twenty big guys would jump out.

20:51.880 --> 20:53.480
I actually believed him back then, you know?

20:53.480 --> 20:54.120
Later, he

20:54.880 --> 20:56.400
got into Berklee College of Music.

20:56.400 --> 20:58.260
He became an excellent musician.

20:59.000 --> 21:00.240
The most awesome and smartest one

21:00.240 --> 21:02.400
is this guy sleeping right opposite my bed.

21:02.400 --> 21:05.280
He was among the first batch of e-commerce livestreamers.

21:05.280 --> 21:07.240
Now he's making a fortune.

21:07.880 --> 21:09.400
He rakes in money every day,

21:09.400 --> 21:11.280
with over 20 livestreamers working for him.

21:11.280 --> 21:12.610
Isn't that impressive?

21:14.120 --> 21:16.400
Our dorm building is also very beautiful.

21:16.400 --> 21:18.930
The entire building is covered in Boston ivy.

21:19.640 --> 21:21.880
This Boston ivy doesn't dissipate heat.

21:21.880 --> 21:22.920
When summer comes,

21:22.920 --> 21:24.250
it gets incredibly hot.

21:24.360 --> 21:26.040
The whole window gets completely covered.

21:26.040 --> 21:27.720
You have to take scissors

21:27.720 --> 21:28.640
and cut it off piece by piece.

21:28.640 --> 21:30.440
Otherwise, no breeze can come in at all.

21:30.440 --> 21:30.840
Right,

21:31.440 --> 21:33.700
you guys have AC in your dorms now, right?

21:34.600 --> 21:36.200
Back in our day, let alone AC,

21:36.200 --> 21:37.720
even the electric fans didn't work well.

21:37.720 --> 21:38.480
We were so hot.

21:38.480 --> 21:39.240
You know how hot it got?

21:39.240 --> 21:40.300
Push the door open,

21:40.440 --> 21:42.200
and it was like an erotic painting.

21:42.200 --> 21:44.000
All the guys had no clothes on.

21:44.800 --> 21:46.330
Of course, they wore pants.

21:46.360 --> 21:47.160
Do you know how hot

21:47.160 --> 21:48.640
we ended up getting?

21:49.040 --> 21:50.280
Your whole dorm went

21:50.800 --> 21:51.800
and booked a room.

21:54.080 --> 21:54.940
Have I told you?

21:55.280 --> 21:56.480
You've said it twice.

22:01.400 --> 22:02.930
But I haven't told Xiaocen.

22:03.120 --> 22:04.160
Xiaocen, did you know

22:04.160 --> 22:05.520
it was so hot that the five of us guys

22:05.520 --> 22:06.850
had to go get a hotel room

22:06.960 --> 22:08.520
and squeeze into one standard room?

22:08.520 --> 22:09.240
Could we even fit?

22:09.240 --> 22:10.000
Not at all.

22:10.600 --> 22:11.960
In the end, I slept in the bathtub.

22:11.960 --> 22:13.020
And then I fell ill.

22:13.400 --> 22:15.400
I must have a bathtub when buying a house.

22:15.400 --> 22:17.130
Otherwise, it feels too small.

22:24.520 --> 22:27.320
I didn't expect the boss to chat for so long.

22:27.840 --> 22:28.600
Maybe he

22:29.520 --> 22:30.850
feels bored sometimes.

22:33.440 --> 22:34.440
He told me before.

22:35.480 --> 22:37.740
He's been in Jingdezhen for seven years.

22:39.560 --> 22:41.220
He used to have a big business.

22:41.760 --> 22:43.220
Then he suddenly fell ill.

22:43.480 --> 22:44.720
Those close to him

22:44.880 --> 22:46.040
gradually left him.

22:48.200 --> 22:49.330
After he recovered,

22:50.400 --> 22:51.930
he left everything behind.

22:52.880 --> 22:53.540
He came here

22:54.280 --> 22:55.480
and opened this shop.

22:58.040 --> 22:59.700
Maybe everyone who comes here

23:01.000 --> 23:02.480
has their own past.

23:10.080 --> 23:10.880
You know what?

23:11.040 --> 23:12.680
We have a tradition in Jingdezhen

23:12.680 --> 23:14.000
that has lasted for thousands of years.

23:14.000 --> 23:15.660
It is to reuse old kiln bricks.

23:15.840 --> 23:16.840
Because for traditional wood-fired kilns,

23:16.840 --> 23:19.040
after firing porcelain about 80 times,

23:19.280 --> 23:20.480
the bricks used to build them

23:20.480 --> 23:22.800
will reach their life cycle

23:23.000 --> 23:25.260
and be naturally replaced from the kiln.

23:25.720 --> 23:28.360
Then these old kiln bricks with kiln sweat

23:28.360 --> 23:30.080
are combined with new ones

23:30.200 --> 23:33.000
to become building materials for local residents.

23:33.000 --> 23:34.080
I see.

23:34.440 --> 23:37.080
The imperial kiln is the origin of our city, Jingdezhen.

23:37.080 --> 23:38.040
But I feel

23:38.280 --> 23:40.200
it better preserves the memory

23:40.200 --> 23:41.530
and warmth of this city.

23:41.880 --> 23:44.040
Every time I visit and walk around here,

23:44.040 --> 23:45.760
it feels like I can really travel through time.

23:45.760 --> 23:47.000
It's as if I can truly see the ancients

23:47.000 --> 23:48.360
working hard here.

23:49.600 --> 23:50.600
The ones displayed in this row

23:50.600 --> 23:52.120
are all modern ceramics.

24:06.040 --> 24:06.640
Look.

24:07.080 --> 24:09.410
This one is 'Spring Brings Good Fortune'.

24:09.880 --> 24:11.210
It's really beautiful.

24:13.720 --> 24:14.320
By the way,

24:14.920 --> 24:16.280
can I ask you for a favor?

24:16.880 --> 24:17.560
What is it?

24:17.960 --> 24:19.120
If you have time,

24:19.400 --> 24:21.080
could you take me to your school's museum

24:21.080 --> 24:21.920
for a visit?

24:22.800 --> 24:24.280
Our school's museum?

24:24.600 --> 24:25.000
Yes.

24:25.560 --> 24:26.640
Your school's museum

24:26.640 --> 24:27.880
has many precious collections.

24:27.880 --> 24:29.610
I've always wanted to see them.

24:31.640 --> 24:33.320
Because only people from the school can make a reservation,

24:33.320 --> 24:34.080
so...

24:35.080 --> 24:35.410
Okay.

24:36.200 --> 24:36.800
Thank you.

24:36.960 --> 24:38.000
No problem. Let's go.
